            "content": "<current_document path=\"Aether and Iron/Manuscript/Core Rules/core_rules.md\">\n# Core Rules: Aether & Iron\n\n## 1. Attributes\nPlayers distribute points into four primary stats. Each stat influences specific \"Save DCs.\"\n\n| Attribute | Modifier Formula | Use Case |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Might** | $(Score - 10) / 2$ | Melee, Athletics, Physical Saves |\n| **Agility** | $(Score - 10) / 2$ | Stealth, Ranged, Reflex Saves |\n| **Essence** | $(Score - 10) / 2$ | Magic Power, Mental Resistance |\n| **Wit** | $(Score - 10) / 2$ | Investigation, Initiative |\n\n## 2. Combat Mechanics\nCombat is turn-based. Action economy includes:\n1.  **Standard Action** (Attack, Spell)\n2.  **Minor Action** (Drink Potion, Draw Weapon)\n3.  **Reaction** (Counter-spell, Parry)\n\n### Damage Calculation\nThe standard damage formula for physical strikes is:\n$$Damage = (Base\\,Dice) + \\text{Attribute Mod}$$Here is an expanded explanation of the damage calculation mechanics in the \"Aether & Iron\" RPG system:\n\n### Damage Calculation\n\nAt the core of the combat system is the damage calculation formula, which determines the amount of harm inflicted by physical attacks and strikes. This formula reflects the balance between the raw power of the attacker and the finesse with which they wield their weapon.\n\nThe standard damage formula is as follows:\n\n$$Damage = (Base\\,Dice) + \\text{Attribute Mod}$$\n\nThe **Base Dice** represents the inherent damage potential of the weapon or unarmed strike being used. This could be a d4 for a dagger, a d8 for a longsword, or a d6 for a fist strike, for example. The size of this dice die reflects the inherent lethality and destructive capacity of the attack.\n\nThe **Attribute Modifier** is derived from the attacker's relevant ability score. For melee attacks, this is typically the character's Might score, which measures their physical strength and martial prowess. For ranged attacks, the Agility modifier would be used, as it reflects the shooter's dexterity and precision.\n\nThis combination of raw damage dice and refined attribute modifier creates a balanced equation that accounts for both the power of the blow and the skill of the combatant. A mighty warrior wielding a greatsword will deal tremendous damage, but a nimble rogue striking with a swift dagger can also inflict serious harm through careful, targeted strikes.\n\nThe damage formula is a core mechanic that underpins the combat system, allowing players to intuitively understand how their choices in character building and equipment selection will translate to battlefield effectiveness. It is a simple yet versatile formula that can be adapted to handle a wide range of weapon types and combat styles within the \"Aether & Iron\" world.\n\n</current_document>\n",
            "role": "user"
        }
